Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
789 Botany Road is a stunning warehouse conversion offering high clearance, exposed timber sawtooth ceilings and fantastic natural light. It is a diverse property that that has attracted two high profile furniture groups and an independent national charity. 

The last remaining suite of 225sqm could suit a multitude of uses, from commercial office tenants to furniture/lighting/kitchen/bathroom/fashion tenants looking to join Rosebery’s newest Designer Hub.

Tenancy Schedule:
GF – LEASED to Homeware Gallery
GF and Level 1 – LEASED to Boyd Blue
Level 1 – LEASED to Kids Cancer Project
Level 1 – LAST REMAINING SUITE OF 225sqm

Located in the southern Sydney suburb of Rosebery on Botany Road, 789 is well positioned within one of Sydney’s major urban renewal growth areas. The new Green Square Town Centre development is creating 20,000 jobs and accommodating 60,000 residents, whilst the City of Sydney will add an aquatic centre, parks, playgrounds and childcare.

Key Features of 789 Botany:
•	225sqm remaining with expansive frontage to Botany Road and its thousands of daily passers-by
•	Dual street access
•	Premium quality facilities and finishes
•	Polished concrete & timber floors with exposed timber trusses
•	End of trip facilities
•	Air-conditioned throughout
•	Kitchenette
•	4 secure undercover car spaces 

As far as locational benefits for your staff and customers, 789 is next to some of the best coffee shops, retailers and eateries in Sydney.

Key Surrounding Amenities include:
•	The Cannery food centre	
•	Black Star Pastry
•	Three Blue Ducks
•	IGA
•	Dan Murphys
•	Harvey Norman
•	Bunnings Warehouse
•	Officeworks
•	Domayne
•	Alexandria Homemaker Centre

For further information please contact your exclusive marketing agents.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Locate your business in this chic corner suite fronting Botany Road in the highly sought-after Rosebery precinct.

Benefiting from high foot and road traffic situated on the corner of Botany Road and Morley Avenue, take advantage of the location, local amenity and proximity to public transport.

Property highlights:

• 134sqm of open plan floor area
• 15sqm exclusive courtyard
• Suitable for creative office, retail, showroom
• Mechanical ventilation and grease trap suitable for food users
• Saw tooth roof with high ceilings
• Bathed in natural light with floor to ceiling windows
• Secure basement parking and storage
• Dual street entrances for customers
• Situated in the booming Rosebery precinct
• 1km from Green Square Station
